Not sure why this place doesn’t have the 5 stars it deserves. This place is AUTHENTIC Mexican food approved by someone of Mexican descent. They do not play with the portions and spiciness, which I appreciate because many other Mexican restaurants in the area don’t make their food as spicy out of consideration for other people’s tolerance. Order the traditional heavy meals, such as chilaquiles, chile de puerco, the rotisserie chicken with rice & beans. Know that you’ll do yourself a disservice if you order something like a chicken quesadilla.... You have a whole family here making cozy, comforting, homemade Mexican food, so don’t order something basically tex-mex and expect it to be bomb. I’ve ordered several times and this place never disappoints me.

When a customer needs something done, it should get done. When a customer calls over the phone to order some food, it should be started right away especially when the restaurant was not busy at all.  On a Sunday evening at 7pm, I had called this place to to order simple tacos over the phone. I get there in about 20 minutes and the tacos were not even ready nor cooked. Of course there is never any sort of manager around because people are to busy chatting in the kitchen, who knows about what.  Nobody in there has the decency go even apologize or recognize the customer. I do not pay play the race card but I guess since I'm not from their culture I'm left for last or not even considered as a customer.  This is not the first time this has happened. People hear especially the males are extremely lazy and take their sweet time.  I've been in this industry way too long and I'm well respected to be treated this way with such unprofessionalism.  A place does not mess with someone's order and decide to not cook it at all.  Managers and owners need to come out of their hole and be productive and run a Mexican restaurant the way it should be.
